$ SQL Developer: Tools -> Preferences -> Database -> Advanced

Settings that can be configured under *Tools -> Preferences -> Database -> Advanced* include:
  • SQL Array Fetch Size (50 … 200)
  • How → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/null[`null`] values are displayed (text and/or background color)
  • How struct and → development/XML values are displayed in the grid
  • If *autocommit* should be made
  • Location of the → development/security/kerberos config file (`krb5.conf`)
  • Location for kerberos credential cache files
  • If or not the *Oracle client* should be used
  • If or not the *OCI/thick driver* should be used
  • Location of the *tnsnames* directory

sa:
  → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer/directories/user-information/systemV_W_X_Y_Z/o_sqldeveloper/product-preferences_xml#sqldev-pred-pref-kerberos[Kerberos related] settings
  in → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer/directories/user-information/systemV_W_X_Y_Z/o_sqldeveloper/product-preferences_xml[`SystemV.W.X.Y.Z/o.sqldeveloper/product-preferences.xml`].
